                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/9361.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to Great
                            Britain</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-24T20:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1913—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. Department’s October 24, 6 p.m. Would you favor authorizing me to ascertain
                    whether the British Government as an act of friendliness <pb facs="0954" n="850"
                        xml:id="pg_850"/> will refrain from recognizing anyone claiming to be
                    elected President of Mexico at the elections of October 26 until our Government
                    has had reasonable time to consider its course?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
